    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AgentRegistry
    Central registry for managing available AI agent types and their factories.
    AgentSelectionDialog
    Dialog for selecting an AI agent type and configuration.
    AgentSelectionDialog.AgentSelection
     
    AIAdaptationConfig
    Configuration class for AI agent setup and adaptation.
    AIAdaptationConfig.Builder
    Builder pattern for constructing AIAdaptationConfig instances.
    AIAgent
    Interface for all AI agents that can play the game.
    AIAgentFactory
    Factory interface for creating AI agents.
    AIBoardAdapter
    Interface for board access by AI agents.
    AIMoveCoordinator
    AIMoveCoordinator: manages AI agents, handles move requests on background threads, and ensures moves are applied on the JavaFX Application thread.
    AITester
    Framework for testing AI agents against each other.
    AITester.TestResult
    Represents the result of a testing session.
    AITestScreenBuilder
    Builder for the AI Testing screen dialog.
    AITestScreenBuilder.AITestSelection
    Container for the AI test selection.
    AlphaZeroConfig
    Configuration class for AlphaZero setup.
    AlphaZeroConfig.Builder
    Builder class for creating AlphaZeroConfig instances.
    AlphaZeroMCTS
    Implements a Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) specifically designed for AlphaZero.
    AlphaZeroNet
    Encapsulates the DeepLearning4J computation graph for the AlphaZero neural network.
    AlphaZeroPlayer
    An AI agent powered by the AlphaZero algorithm.
    AlphaZeroPlayerFactory
    Factory for creating AlphaZeroPlayer instances.
    AlphaZeroRunner
    Entry point for running AlphaZero training sessions from the command line.
    AlphaZeroTrainer
    Orchestrates the AlphaZero training pipeline.
    AppStyles
    Centralized utility class for applying application-wide JavaFX styles.
    Backpropagation
    Implements the backpropagation phase of Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS).
    BaseSimulation
    Implements a basic random simulation strategy for Monte Carlo Tree Search.
    Batcher
    Defines the interface for batched neural network inference.
    Board
    Represents the Hex game board, managing the grid state, move history, and connectivity checks.
    Board.MoveSnapshot
     
    BoardAdapter
    Adapter that exposes game.core.Board through AIBoardAdapter for AI agents.
    BoardConverters
    Shared utilities for converting adapters to Board efficiently.
    BoardEncoder
    Utility for converting game board states into neural network input tensors.
    BoardStateView
    A wrapper view for the Board class that exposes state and logic required for the UI, without directly exposing internal AI mechanisms.
    Buttons
    Utility factory class for creating consistently styled JavaFX buttons.
    CaseOpeningView
    View for the Case Opening feature.
    CaseOpeningView.Item
    Container for an item in the case opening.
    CaseOpeningView.Rarity
     
    CentralityHeuristic
    A heuristic that favors moves closer to the center of the board.
    Color
    Represents the possible states of a cell on the Hex game board.
    ConnectivityHeuristic
    A heuristic that favors moves adjacent to the current player's existing stones.
    DifficultyDialog
    Dialog for selecting the difficulty level for MCTS AI.
    DirectBatcher
    A simple implementation of Batcher that processes requests immediately on the calling thread (or strictly sequentially).
    Expansion
    Implements the expansion phase of Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS).
    GameController
    GameController: owns turn logic + mediates between ui.BoardView and bridge.BoardAdapter.
    GameController.GameEndListener
    Listener for game end events.
    GameScreenBuilder
    Builder for the Game screen.
    GameScreenBuilder.GameScreen
    Container for the Game screen components.
    GameSession
    Represents a single playable game session for the UI layer.
    GameState
    Encapsulates the state of a Hex game for use within the MCTS simulation.
    Heuristic
    A heuristic interface for evaluating the quality of moves in a game state.
    HexBoardView
    JavaFX view component that renders an interactive Hex board.
    LinearCombinationHeuristic
    A composite heuristic that combines multiple individual heuristics using weighted linear combination.
    MainMenu
    JavaFX application entry point for the Connections game.
    MCTS
    Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) implementation for game tree exploration.
    MCTSPlayer
    An AI agent implementation based on Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS).
    MCTSPlayerFactory
    Factory implementation for creating MCTSPlayer agents.
    MCTSTuner
    A hyperparameter tuning utility for MCTS MovePruner heuristics.
    MenuScreenBuilder
    Builder for the Menu screen.
    Move
    An immutable representation of a move coordinate (row, column) in the game.
    MovePruner
    A move pruning utility that reduces the branching factor in game tree search by filtering out less promising moves based on heuristic evaluation.
    MoveRegistration
    Manages move registration, validation, and history tracking for a Hex game.
    MultiGpuBatcher
    A high-performance batcher that distributes inference across multiple worker threads, potentially utilizing multiple GPUs.
    NavigationService
    Service for navigating between different UI screens.
    NeuralNetBatcher
    A worker that aggregates individual inference requests into efficient batches for processing by a single neural network instance.
    NeuralNetBatcher.BatchJob
    Internal class representing a batch job.
    NeuralNetBatcher.Output
    Container for the results of a neural network prediction.
    NeuralNetBatcher.Request
    Internal class representing a single inference request.
    Node
    Represents a node in the Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) game tree.
    OptimizedSimulation
    Implements an optimized simulation strategy for Monte Carlo Tree Search that uses move pruning and heuristic evaluation to guide simulations.
    PlayAgainDialog
    Dialog that appears after a game ends, showing the winner, score, and options to play again or return to menu.
    Player
    Represents the two players in a Hex game, along with their associated identifiers and stone colors.
    PrunerConfig
    Represents a complete configuration of hyperparameters for MCTS with move pruning and heuristic enhancements.
    RandomPlayer
    A simple AI agent implementation that selects moves uniformly at random.
    RandomPlayerFactory
    Factory implementation for creating RandomPlayer agents.
    Rules
    Utility class containing static methods to validate moves and enforce game rules.
    RunExperimentCSV
    A tool to run various AI experiments and output results in CSV format.
    ScoreBoard
    Maintains cumulative win statistics across multiple games.
    Selection
    Implements the selection phase of Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS).
    ShortestPath
     
    ShortestPathHeuristic
    A heuristic that evaluates moves based on their impact on the shortest path to winning for the current player.
    Simulation
    Interface for simulation strategies in Monte Carlo Tree Search.
    TrainingExampleData
    A data container representing a single training example generated during self-play.
    TunerTester
    Test driver for the MCTSTuner that demonstrates hyperparameter tuning for MCTS configurations.
    UiDefaults
    Default UI configuration constants.
    UnionFind
    A Union-Find (Disjoint Set Union) data structure implementation.
